(a)  A university, hospital, or institution authorized to receive unclaimed bodies as provided in this part may refuse to accept any such body for the following reasons:



	(1)	Death occurs outside the island on which the university, hospital, or institution is located;
	(2)	The body is autopsied or embalmed;
	(3)	The body is not intact;
	(4)	The university, hospital, or institution has insufficient facilities to handle, store, and use the body; or
	(5)	Medical or health reasons endanger or threaten to endanger the public health and safety.



	(b)  In case of such refusal, the university, hospital, or institution shall notify the appropriate public agency which shall provide for the final disposition of the body pursuant to law. [L 1967, c 240, pt of §1; HRS ]
